---

<script>
  import { getPerson } from "../services/Person";
  const username = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search).get("username")!;


  const person = getPerson(username);

  document.getElementById("displayname")!.innerHTML += `${person.NickName === "" ? 
	person.FirstName : 
	person.NickName} ${person.Surname}`;

	document.getElementById("admissiondate")!.innerHTML += 
	new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-za', { weekday:"long", year:"numeric", month:"short", day:"numeric"})	;

</script>

<Layout title="Code of Conduct">
  <main>
    <Sidebar />
    <br>
	<div><p>
    <h7>Code of Conduct</h7></p>
<br>
<p>Your safety, confort and wellbeing are of the utmost importance to us. <br>This document has been developed to serve as an introduction to the unit and as a source of information for you and your family.<br>
Please read through it carefully and ensure that you are familiar with its contents.<br>
Please feel fee to ask any questions related to the information contained herein.<br>
<br>
<h8>Welcome to Life Glynnview</h8>
<br>
<br>
<h9>Your treating team</h9>
<br>
<br>
Your professional team of dediated, committed individuals are expertly trained in their field. The multi-disciplinary team is typically made up of a psychiatrist, nursing manager and nursing team, psychologist, social worker, and at times  dietician, occupational therapist, physiotherapist, biokineticist and others if needed. Your recovery is dependant on your motivation and participation.  Please note that it is against hospital policy to change your treating team during an admission.
<br>
<br>
<h9>Your therapeutic programme</h9>
<br>
<br>
Your treatment consists of attending therapeutic groups, individual sessions with therapists and medication, as prescribed by your psychiatrist. It is your responsibility to ensure that you adhere to the times allocated to you.  Group therapy is considered compulsory and is seen as an indication of your commitment to your recovery. Please ensure that you arrive on time.
<br>
<br>
<h9><i>Please note that the daily hospital fee does not include doctor or therapist visits. It is the responsibility of the patient and the family to familiarise themselves with the rules of their medical aid schemes.</h9></p></div>
</i> 
</main>
</Layout>

